Step 1: Access Rancher UI
Open: https://3.91.9.26:30017/
Log in with your admin credentials.

####
Step 2: Enable Helm Chart Repositories

Go to Apps & Marketplace → Charts → Repositories.
Make sure Longhorn chart repo is available:
Name: longhorn
URL: https://charts.longhorn.io
If not, add it manually:
Click Add Repository → fill in Name + URL → Save

####
Step 3: Install Longhorn via Rancher

Go to Apps & Marketplace → Charts.
Select Longhorn.
Choose the RKE2 cluster you want to deploy Longhorn to.
Namespace: longhorn-system (default).
Configure settings if needed (optional):
StorageClass name
Number of replicas per volume (default: 3)
Enable default UI (for monitoring)
Click Install.
